result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Raleigh S Elliot in court with attorney Gavin Grubofski.  Galen Bayne-Allison appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 16CM56 and 16CM57 @ 1:35 p.m. Agreement stated - Def has prepaid restitution owed in both. Def will plead to 16CM56 both cts, 16CM57 - dismiss and read in. 16CM56 - 90 days jail on each ct, concurrent, 24 days credit. State does not object to time to report. Court costs. State has complied with VWNR, victim has filed impact statement. Atty Grubofski and Def agree. Plea quest. reviewed. 16CM56 ct 1 - guilty plea. Ct 2 - guilty plea. Court grants motion to dismiss and read in both cts in 16CM57. Constitutional rights, elements, possible penalties reviewed. Atty Grubofski satisfied. Court finds Def understands and pleas freely & voluntarily made. Factual basis. Court accepts pleas and finds guilty of 16CM56 ct 1 disorderly conduct and ct 2 criminal damage to property. Sentencing remarks by Counsel. Statement by Defendant. Court questions Def. Court will follow agreement. Ct 1 - 90 days jail, credit for 24 days served, huber, good time according to jail policy. Court costs. DNA sample and surcharge. Ct 2 - 90 days jail, concurrent to ct 1, 24 days credit, huber. Restitution has been paid on both cases. Court costs and DNA surcharge on ct 2. Report no later than 7 p.m. on 12/19/16. Postconviction rights. Apply bond, pp for balance.
Plea/sentencing hearing on October 21, 2016 at 01:30 pm.
